@node m030104 "Menüunterpunkt: Trace Mouse"
@{" Main " link main}@{" Legal " link legalstuff}@{" Intro " link introduction}@{" Menu " link m1f3f1f}@{" Keys " link keyboard}@{" Windows " link windows}@{" FAQ " link faq}@{" History " link history}@{" Register " link register}
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
                        Menüunterpunkt: Trace Mouse
---------------------------------------------------------------------------

If this option is enabled, the  Objects,  Raw  Blocks  and  Block  Elements
windows  will  open at the current mouse position. This feature can only be
sensibly used when working on a lowres display mode, with just little  view
of  the  whole  level.  Otherwise  you're  adviced  not to use this option,
because it's very irritating.

If you think you want this feature on, you better turn  off  the  automatic
window  opening for the three windows, and open them with the hotkeys, when
you need them.

The behaviour of Trace Mouse might change in futher versions of the Editor.
@endnode 
